<?xml version="1.0"?>
<section xml:id="active-code_javascript">
  <title>JavaScript</title>
  <p>We have come to realize that not everyone loves Python as much as we do.
            So we have now made it possible to write activecode examples in pure javascript as well
            as Python.  Here is a simple example:</p>
  <program xml:id="jstest1" interactive="activecode" language="javascript">
    <input>
var x = 10;
var y = 11;
var z = x + y;
console.log(z);
function fact(n) {
   if(n &lt;= 1) return 1;
   else {
       return n * fact(n-1);
   }
}
console.log(fact(10));
writeln('hello world');
        </input>
  </program>
  <p>Adding a javascript example is just as easy as Python, all you need to do is add a <c>:language:</c>
            parameter to the activecode directive.</p>
  <hint>
